                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The New Raspberry Pi 500+ Has a Built-in Mechanical Keyboard]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-new-raspberry-pi-500-has-a-built-in-mechanical-keyboard/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/raspberry-pi-500-computer.jpg" length="196" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Raspberry Pi]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's billed as "the ultimate Raspberry Pi all-in-one PC."
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Raspberry Pi 500 was the first Pi computer with an integrated keyboard, and now there’s an upgraded model to get excited about. The new Raspberry Pi 500+ has arrived with a higher-quality mechanical keyboard, better internal hardware, and all-important RGB lights.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 17:20:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-new-raspberry-pi-500-has-a-built-in-mechanical-keyboard/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Amazon's Fire OS Replacement for TVs Could Arrive Soon]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/amazons-fire-os-replacement-for-tvs-could-arrive-soon/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/an-amazon-fire-tv-soundbar-plus-with-built-in-subwoofer-under-a-tv-mounted-on-a-wall.jpg" length="478" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Fire TV]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A job listing confirmed it again.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Amazon is preparing to replace Android with its own custom-built Vega OS on Fire TV devices, and an accidental job posting for a software development manager for Prime Video just leaked it. We've been hearing rumors about this for a while, but it should arrive before the end of the year.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 16:28:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/amazons-fire-os-replacement-for-tvs-could-arrive-soon/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Anker Introduces Its Insanely Convenient Nebula X1 Pro Outdoor Projector]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/anker-soundcore-nebula-x1-pro-launch/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Andrew Heinzman]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1.jpg" length="251" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[NEBULA X1]]></category><category><![CDATA[Anker]]></category><category><![CDATA[Soundcore]]></category><category><![CDATA[Projector]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A rolling cart projector with wireless 7.1.4 surround sound speakers. Nice!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Anker is now offering the Nebula X1 Pro, a high-end rolling cart projector designed for indoor and outdoor venues with screens up to 300 inches. It costs $5,000 and is available for pre-order today.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 16:24:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/anker-soundcore-nebula-x1-pro-launch/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Here’s How You Can Find Underrated Films Without Using an Algorithm]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/heres-how-you-can-find-underrated-films-without-using-an-algorithm/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Faisal Rasool]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/hand-holding-a-magnifying-glass-with-popcorn-flying-out-of-a-film-strip-in-front-of-blurred-movie-posters.png" length="1906" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[reddit]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Try this instead of rewatching your comfort show for the twelfth time.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you’ve ever felt that the streaming services you’re subscribed to seem to always give you more of the same, you’re not the only one. These platforms use algorithms that serve you content similar to what you’ve already liked. It creates a sort of narrow bubble or loop, which leaves little room for genuine surprise and discovery. Let’s change that, and help you find films you’ll love without the help of an algorithm.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 16:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/heres-how-you-can-find-underrated-films-without-using-an-algorithm/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Lenovo Chromebook Is Just $139 Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-lenovo-chromebook-is-just-139-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/lenovo-ideapad-slim-3-on-painted-background.jpg" length="187" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Chromebook & Chrome OS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><category><![CDATA[Chromebook]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This is a major price drop for a great Chromebook.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Lenovo's IdeaPad Slim 3 Chromebook price has dropped by a massive 57%, but it likely won't last long. You can get this Chromebook for just <a href="https://bestbuy.7tiv.net/c/156932/614286/10014?subId1=UUhtgUeUpU2016878&subId2=ehtg&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fproduct%2Flenovo-ideapad-slim-3-chromebook-14-full-hd-laptop-mediatek-kompanio-520-4gb-memory-64gb-emmc-abyss-blue%2FJJGSH8G34Z" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">$139.00 at Best Buy</a>, which is a major discount from its original price of $319.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 15:21:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-lenovo-chromebook-is-just-139-today/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Is the First Phone With a Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-the-first-phone-with-a-qualcomm-snapdragon-8-elite-gen-5/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/xiaomi-17-hero.jpg" length="127" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's not even 2026 yet.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5 will power 2026's best phones, but that won't stop some companies from releasing theirs while this year is not over. Xiaomi is the first company to release a phone powered by Qualcomm's latest chip—meet the Xiaomi 17 series.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 15:17:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-the-first-phone-with-a-qualcomm-snapdragon-8-elite-gen-5/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Use the Arrow Keys More Than Any Other Keys in Excel]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-excel-arrow-keys-keyboard-shortcuts/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tony Phillips]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/close-up-of-a-keyboard-with-arrow-keys-highlighted-in-green-next-to-the-microsoft-excel-logo-1.png" length="1210" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft Excel]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft 365]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft Office]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Arrow keys in Excel aren't just for moving to the next cell.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><!--StartFragment -->I love using keyboard shortcuts when working in Microsoft Excel, as they help me speed up my workflow and prevent me from having to alternate between my keyboard and mouse. One group of keys I find more useful than most is the Arrow keys. Here's what they can do.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 15:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-excel-arrow-keys-keyboard-shortcuts/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft Will Offer Extended Windows 10 Updates To More People]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-will-offer-extended-windows-10-updates-to-more-people/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/3-2-windows-10.jpg" length="739" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 10]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Probably not for you, though.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The clock is ticking on Windows 10. We're less than a month away from the operating system's official EOL date on October 14th, after which point, unless you're eligible for extended updates, you'll stop getting security updates unless they're absolutely critical. Now, some regions are eligible for at least an extra year of updates, but probably not you.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 14:31:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-will-offer-extended-windows-10-updates-to-more-people/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Used Luxury Hybrid Sedan Costs Less Than a New Toyota Corolla]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/used-luxury-hybrid-sedan-costs-less-than-new-toyota-corolla/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2016_lexus_es_300h_010_41f748f065b0747e843a92ae4332ded2dcff3e02.jpg" length="71" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hybrid Cars]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The 2018 Lexus ES 300h is a smarter, more luxurious used buy than a brand-new Corolla.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/fuel-sipping-hybrid-smartest-budget-buy/" target="_blank">Toyota Corolla</a> is still holding its own in today’s car market—even against the wave of <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/tag/suvs/" target="_blank">crossovers and SUVs</a>. It’s affordable, reliable, and efficient—all the things people expect from a Corolla.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 14:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/used-luxury-hybrid-sedan-costs-less-than-new-toyota-corolla/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How I Created a Detailed Dashboard for All of My Self-Hosted Apps]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/how-i-created-a-detailed-dashboard-for-all-of-my-self-hosted-apps/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/illustration-of-a-windows-11-laptop-and-logos-of-some-open-source-apps-around-it-1.png" length="721" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Self Hosted]]></category><category><![CDATA[Docker]]></category><category><![CDATA[Homelab]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Who needs bookmarks when you have a dashboard?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Are you tired of trying to remember IPs and ports for your self-hosted apps? I finally figured out how to make my homelab easier to manage—a detailed dashboard of all my services.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 14:00:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/how-i-created-a-detailed-dashboard-for-all-of-my-self-hosted-apps/</guid></item></channel>
